<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1451,863,1030]" pageId="1" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,243,863,885]" pageId="1" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hamzaoglu &amp; Koc" authorityYear="2022" box="[267,454,864,885]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Hesperis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="muglensis">
<emphasis box="[267,454,864,885]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="31">Hesperis muglensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber-Morath" authorityYear="1965" box="[581,686,864,885]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Hesperis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pisidica">
<emphasis box="[581,686,864,885]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="31">H. pisidica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in terms of its habit. However, it mainly differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber-Morath" authorityYear="1965" box="[1206,1311,864,885]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Hesperis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pisidica">
<emphasis box="[1206,1311,864,885]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="31">H. pisidica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because it has stems with densely glandular, simple and a few bifurcate hairs in lower part (not stellate, simple and glandular), sepals 4–6-veined and 1.8–2.2. mm wide (not 7–12-veined and 
<quantity box="[621,718,936,957]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" unit="mm" value="3.2" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.4">2.4–4 mm</quantity>
wide), anthers 
<quantity box="[867,982,936,957]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.95" metricValueMax="3.1" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" unit="mm" value="2.95" valueMax="3.1" valueMin="2.8">2.8‒3.1 mm</quantity>
long (not 
<quantity box="[1081,1178,936,958]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" unit="mm" value="3.75" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.5">3.5‒4 mm</quantity>
long) (
<tableCitation box="[1248,1319,936,958]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="3.[136,224,158,182]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="TABLE 1. Diagnostic characters of Hesperis muglensiss and H. pisidica." pageId="1" pageNumber="31">Table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
